<subSubSection pageId="39" pageNumber="340" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,1799,2042]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1872,1898]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kolenati, F. A. R." box="[322,500,1871,1897]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" refId="ref19719" refString="Kolenati, F. A. R. (1846) Meletemata entomologica. Facscicule III. Brachelytra Caucasi cum distribution geographica adnexis pselaphinis, scydmaenis, notoxidibus et xylophagis. Typis Imperialis Academiae Scientarium, Petropoli, 44 pp., pls. XII - XIV." type="book" year="1846">Kolenati (1846)</bibRefCitation>
originally described “ 
<emphasis box="[750,890,1871,1897]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Goryphaena</emphasis>
” 
<taxonomicName authority="Kolenati, 1846" authorityName="Kolenati" authorityYear="1846" box="[909,1179,1871,1897]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Gyrophaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glacialis">
<emphasis box="[909,1005,1871,1897]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">glacialis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kolenati, F. A. R." box="[1013,1179,1871,1897]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" refId="ref19719" refString="Kolenati, F. A. R. (1846) Meletemata entomologica. Facscicule III. Brachelytra Caucasi cum distribution geographica adnexis pselaphinis, scydmaenis, notoxidibus et xylophagis. Typis Imperialis Academiae Scientarium, Petropoli, 44 pp., pls. XII - XIV." type="book" year="1846">Kolenati, 1846</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(now synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Mannerheim, 1830)" authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Mannerheim" baseAuthorityYear="1830" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Oligota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inflata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Oligota inflata</emphasis>
(Mannerheim, 1830)
</taxonomicName>
, e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Schulke, M. &amp; Smetana, A." box="[585,900,1907,1934]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" refId="ref20057" refString="Schulke, M. &amp; Smetana, A. (2015) Staphylinidae. In: Lobl, I. &amp; Lobl, D. (Eds.), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Vol. 2. Hydrophiloidea - Staphylinoidea. Revised and Updated Edition. Brill, Leiden, pp. 304 - 1134." type="book" year="2015">Schülke &amp; Smetana (2015))</bibRefCitation>
based on unspecified number of 
<typeStatus box="[1276,1374,1908,1934]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">syntypes</typeStatus>
from “…montis Kasbek Caucasi centralis...”. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hochhuth, J. H." box="[600,833,1943,1970]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" pagination="18 - 214" refId="ref19531" refString="Hochhuth, J. H. (1849) Die Staphylinen-Fauna des Kaukasus und Transkaukasiens. Bulletin de la Societe Imperiale des Naturalistes de Moscou, 22 (1), 18 - 214." type="journal article" year="1849">Hochhuth (1849: 73)</bibRefCitation>
misidentified and redescribed it: the studied specimen belongs to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Erichson" authorityYear="1839" box="[275,566,1979,2006]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Gyrophaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="strictula" subGenus="Phaenogyra">
<emphasis box="[275,295,1980,2006]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">G</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[320,457,1979,2005]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">Phaenogyra</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[473,566,1979,2005]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">strictula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The name 
<taxonomicName authority="Hochhuth, 1849" authorityName="Hochhuth" authorityYear="1849" box="[700,1020,1979,2006]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Gyrophaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glacialis">
<emphasis box="[700,720,1980,2006]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[735,831,1979,2005]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">glacialis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hochhuth, J. H." box="[839,1020,1979,2006]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" pagination="18 - 214" refId="ref19531" refString="Hochhuth, J. H. (1849) Die Staphylinen-Fauna des Kaukasus und Transkaukasiens. Bulletin de la Societe Imperiale des Naturalistes de Moscou, 22 (1), 18 - 214." type="journal article" year="1849">Hochhuth, 1849</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
[sic!] was treated as the synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Erichson" authorityYear="1839" box="[151,278,2015,2042]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Gyrophaena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="strictula">
<emphasis box="[151,171,2016,2042]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[185,278,2015,2041]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="340">strictula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Schulke, M. &amp; Smetana, A." box="[342,631,2015,2042]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" refId="ref20057" refString="Schulke, M. &amp; Smetana, A. (2015) Staphylinidae. In: Lobl, I. &amp; Lobl, D. (Eds.), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Vol. 2. Hydrophiloidea - Staphylinoidea. Revised and Updated Edition. Brill, Leiden, pp. 304 - 1134." type="book" year="2015">Schülke &amp; Smetana 2015</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Enushchenko, I. V. &amp; Semenov, V. B." box="[642,1000,2015,2042]" pageId="39" pageNumber="340" pagination="301 - 337" refId="ref18915" refString="Enushchenko, I. V. &amp; Semenov, V. B. (2016) A review of the genus Gyrophaena Mannerhein 1830 (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae: Gyrophaenina) of the Caucasus and adjacent territories. Zootaxa, 4126 (3), 301 - 337. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4126.3.1" type="journal article" year="2016">Enushchenko &amp; Semenov 2016</bibRefCitation>
), but this is an unavailable name.
</paragraph>
